# SearchBar

Side-nav search bar for the Astro API docs. Mirrors Hugo's popup search (the one in [`layouts/partials/search.html`](https://github.com/DataDog/documentation/blob/master/layouts/partials/search.html), embedded in the API side nav) with a thinner, direct-to-Typesense client.

## Behaviors

| Behavior | Notes |
|----------|-------|
| Query input | Debounced ~200ms; closes the popup when blank |
| Result groups | API, Getting Started, Documentation, Guides, Integrations, Partners — empty groups are hidden |
| Group order | API pinned first (the whole Astro site is API), Partners last |
| Cross-site link routing | API hits open same-origin in Astro; all other categories link to `https://docs.datadoghq.com${relpermalink}` (target=_blank) |
| Ask AI placeholder | Rendered at the top of the popup as a `<Placeholder>`-styled stand-in until conversational search is wired up |
| Keyboard shortcuts | `/` and `Cmd/Ctrl+K` focus the input; `Esc` clears + blurs |
| Result navigation | `ArrowDown`/`ArrowUp` walk through Ask AI then hits; `Enter` opens the selected hit |
| Outside click | Closes the popup |

## Typesense plumbing

Queries hit `POST /multi_search` against two collections — `docs_alias` (with the `docs_alias_api_view` preset) and `docs_partners_alias` (with `docs_partners_view`). Per-environment cluster details live in [`src/config/typesense.ts`](https://github.com/DataDog/documentation/blob/master/astro/src/config/typesense.ts) and mirror Hugo's `assets/scripts/config/config-docs.js`.

## Live

The component is mounted inside the API side nav on every API page; the box below shows it standalone for visual checks.

